result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Jay John Koechell was found guilty of OWI (5th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Prior to re-licensing the defendant is to complete an OWI Assessment.

miscConds.notes: Cash Bond posted has been applied.  The remaining balance of the Fine is to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Same repayment provisions apply as noted above for the Fine.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars (restaurant area of a bar or tavern would not be considered a violation), and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  Any possession of prescribed medications must also be in the proper quantity prescribed.
Defendant is ordered to participate and successfully complete the Waushara County TAD/Safe Streets Program.    DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

timeConds.notes: Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges granted.  Balance of sentence to commence forthwith.
